donor_name: JOINT UNITED NATIONS PROGRAMME ON HIV/AIDS
UNDP AS ADMINISTRATIVE AGENT FOR A JOINT PROGRAMME PASS THROUGH ARRANGEMENT
outputs.output_descr: Implemented by the National AIDS Control Council (NACC) and the Ministry of Planning National Development and Vision 2030, the Joint Programme aims to have an equitable human rights and gender based multispectral response to HIV mainstreamed, operationalized and sustained in planning and budgets as well as sectoral programmes and policies. It also aims to enhance capacity building of HIV in the six key sectors of education, agriculture, transport, governance, justice, law and order and security.
